ve broadly served audiences, citizens and licence fee payers well. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We have particular in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">terest in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the BBC’s 6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> public purpose, namely </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">‘the promotion of emergi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ng communications technologies’.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e believe there is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">no doubt that the BBC’s unwav</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ering support for TV Switchover </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ensured the project was a huge success. We commend the BBC’s role in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the targeted assistance scheme to help vulnerable groups buy and i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nstall new equipment. T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">heir advice and support for Digital UK’s marketing and communications activity was also vital in building public awareness of, and readiness for, digital switchover. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he production and promotion of high-quality digital content and services by the BBC has encouraged audiences to obtain the maximum benefit from the opportunities available.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-