e:11pt">coverage</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> both for national and local services.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Arqiva</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> believes the Licence Fee me</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">chanism has served the BBC well and should continue to do so. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The BBC should offer </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">engaging, high quality </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">content, programmes and services available on a wide range of digital platforms</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to serve </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">all</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> licence fee payers across the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> whole of the United Kingdom. Anything which redirects Licence Fee money to other rival broadcasters or purposes may serve to undermine the Corporati</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">on’s core output or objectives.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Arqiva would welcome the government awarding the BBC a renewed 10 year Cha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rter, providing certainty for the Corporation, and certainty for the wider broadcasting, media, communications and technology sector, as well as the wider creative economy.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:1pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:1pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Arqiva believes the UK benefits from a strong BBC, independent of government. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is vital that the process for agreeing the cons</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">titution of the BBC is open and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">transparent.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt; width:437.4pt"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:437.4pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">About Arqiva</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Arqiva is a media infrastructure and technology company operating at the heart of the broadcast and mobile communications industry and at the forefr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ont of network solutions and services in an incr